{"name":"Sylvie’s Baked Sardines","slug":"sylvie-s-baked-sardines","description":"Sardines are a staple in southern France. This recipe is based on a little dish I loved in a bistro in Suzette, France — it makes the perfect pantry dinner, baked and served right in the tin.","ingredients":[{"name":"sardines in olive oil","quantity":"2 cans (4 oz/ 120 g)","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"pitted black olives","quantity":"4","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"sun-dried tomatoes","quantity":"4","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"shallots","quantity":"2","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"3 Onion Dip Mix","quantity":"1 tbsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"Dijon mustard","quantity":"2 tsp","additionalInstruction":null},{"name":"plain crackers","quantity":"4","additionalInstruction":null}],"totalTime":"20 min","servings":"2 servings","preparation":["Preheat oven to 400° F (205° C).","Remove tails and mash sardines (keeping the tiny bones – they give it all the more flavour). Mix in olives, sun-dried tomatoes, shallots, dip mix, and mustard.","Refill cans with sardine mixture, spreading evenly with the back of a spoon. Top with crackers and bake 10 minutes, or until crisp and golden."],"tags":[{"slug":"fish___seafood","name":"Fish & Seafood"},{"slug":"gluten_free_e8446d0","name":"Gluten-free"},{"slug":"appetizers___small_bites","name":"Appetizers & Small Bites"},{"slug":"dinner","name":"Dinner"},{"slug":"lunch","name":"Lunch"},{"slug":"low_sodium","name":"Low-sodium"},{"slug":"sugar_conscious","name":"Sugar Conscious"},{"slug":"dairy_free","name":"Dairy-free"}],"nutritionalInformation":{"servingSize":"","calories":90,"fat":4,"saturatedFat":1,"transFat":0,"cholesterol":15,"sodium":240,"carbohydrate":7,"fiber":1,"sugars":1,"protein":4},"tips":[],"perfectlyBalanceYourPlate":"","imagePath":"../images/Sylvie-s-Baked-Sardines-Main.jpg","products":[{"slug":"n3_onion_dip_mix_c845e80","name":"3 Onion Dip Mix"}]}